Dear Sasi,

Thank you for the M02 RMI module FSD completion schedule. This is noted 
and recorded.

Transaction 1 — Purchase Order FSD is already CEO-approved as of today. 
The remaining five transactions are committed as follows:

   #   Transaction           Target Date
   2   Arrival Entry         21 April 2026
   3   Lot Bale Entry        24 April 2026
   4   Inspection            27 April 2026
   5   Issue Entry           30 April 2026
   6   Purchase Bill Entry   05 May 2026

*Three points for your planning.*

*First: *the schedule is tight — one new FSD every 3–4 working days 
through April and into May. This is achievable if each FSD follows the 
pattern established in the Purchase Order FSD: Stage 0 complete before 
you start, SP code submitted via Follow-up Prompt B, Section 11 in the 
four-column format. The first FSD took weeks to reach approval quality. 
Transactions 2 through 6 must benefit from that learning and reach PM 
submission in fewer cycles.

*Second: *IST reviewer availability is the most likely constraint. For 
M02, PM Saravanan is the IST reviewer. *Saravanan, please plan your IST 
review availability against Sasi's dates above*. If a transaction FSD 
arrives from Sasi on the target date, your IST review must turn around 
within one working day to keep the chain moving.

*Third:* with M02 Purchase Order now approved, you may begin Claude Code 
development for that form alongside the FSD preparation work for 
Transaction 2. Both tracks can run in parallel.

*These dates are now the project commitment for M02. They will be 
reviewed at the next Saturday meeting.
*
Regards,
T. Mani

cc: PM Saravanan (IST availability for M02 transactions 2–6), TL-IST 
Palanivel, Abinandan

