        <blockquote type="cite"
          cite="mid:e82b27bf-c67e-4406-a908-5fcff36c9185@kalsofte.com">
          <meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
            content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
          <p>Dear Team,<br>
            <br>
            Please find below the <b>Minutes of the Review Meeting held
              on 11 April 2026.</b> Review the action items assigned to
            you and ensure they are completed within the stated
            deadlines.<br>
            <br>
            ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────<br>
            MINUTES OF MEETING<br>
            SPINRISE Project Review Meeting<br>
            Date: Saturday, 11 April 2026 | Time: 5:00 PM – 7:00 PM<br>
            Venue: Meeting Room, Kalpatharu Software Ltd, Coimbatore<br>
            Chaired by: T. Mani, Founder &amp; CEO<br>
            Minutes recorded by:CEO on behalf of PM Saravanan<br>
            ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────<br>
            <br>
            Attendees:<br>
            T. Mani (CEO), TL-Dev Sasi, Mariyaiya, Abinandan, Annamalai,
            Sathishkumar, PM Saravanan, Muthuvel, Seenivasan, TL-IST
            Palanivel, Hariharan<br>
            <br>
            <b>1. Opening Remarks and Purpose</b><br>
            <br>
            The CEO opened the meeting by acknowledging the team's
            collective effort during the first two weeks of the SPINRISE
            FSD preparation phase. He outlined that the purpose of the
            meeting was to review the current status of all four
            modules, consolidate learnings from the FSD process, receive
            team feedback on the newly introduced FSD Review Checklist,
            and align on the pace of work going forward. The CEO
            emphasised that Stage 0 is the foundational step for every
            module and that a clean Stage 0 is non-negotiable before any
            FSD draft can be accepted. The first transaction in each of
            the four modules — M01 Purchase Requisition, M02 RMI
            Purchase Order, M03 Domestic Sales Order, M04 Daily
            Attendance Download — must each have a fully signed-off FSD
            as the baseline before development begins.<br>
            <br>
            <b>2. Mail and File Naming Convention — Standardised with
              Immediate Effect</b><br>
            <br>
            The CEO directed that all team communications related to
            SPINRISE must follow a standardised naming convention from
            Monday 13 April, to enable easy tracking and reference
            across the project lifecycle.<br>
            <br>
            Mail Subject Format: SpinRise – [Module ID &amp; Name] –
            [Transaction Name] – [Purpose]<br>
            Example: SpinRise – M01-PO Purchase Requisition – FSD –
            Review<br>
            <br>
            File Attachment Format: SpinRise-[Module ID]-[Module
            Name]-[Transaction Short Name]-[Purpose]-[DD-MM-YY]<br>
            Example: SpinRise-M01-PO-PR-FSD-12-04-26.docx<br>
            <br>
            <b>This convention applies to all mails and attachments from
              all team members without exception.</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>3. Module-wise FSD Status Review</b><br>
            <br>
            M01 — Purchase Order Module (Purchase Requisition)<br>
            Developer Mariyaiya reported that the FSD v2.2 has been
            submitted and that Claude Code usage has been productive.
            The FSD is pending PM sign-off.<br>
            <br>
            M02 — Raw Material Inventory (RMI Purchase Order)<br>
            TL-Dev Sasi reported that FSD v5 has been submitted with all
            IST items resolved including the web approval URL and the
            Section 5.11 PR-to-PO workflow. The FSD is in the process of
            completing PM review.<br>
            <br>
            M03 — Domestic Sales (Sale Order)<br>
            Developer Annamalai confirmed that the v3 FSD was submitted
            before the meeting. PM sign-off is pending.<br>
            <br>
            M04 — Payroll Module (Daily Attendance Download)<br>
            Developer Sathishkumar confirmed that the updated FSD has
            been submitted. PM sign-off is pending.<br>
            <br>
            <b>PM Saravanan confirmed that Stage 4 PM sign-off for all
              four module FSDs — M01, M02, M03, and M04 — will be
              completed on Monday 13 April without any deviation.</b>
            This commitment is recorded in these minutes.<br>
            <br>
            The CEO reiterated that the FSD Review Checklist distributed
            on 11 April is mandatory from Monday 13 April. The target is
            to complete each transaction FSD in a maximum of two
            revision cycles. The back-and-forth mail pattern of the past
            two weeks will not be acceptable going forward. Each team
            member must ensure their submission meets the checklist
            standard before sending.<br>
            <br>
            <b>4. Learnings from Two Weeks of Claude AI Usage<br>
            </b><br>
            The team discussed their experience with Claude AI for FSD
            documentation. The general consensus was that the approach
            is accurate, helpful, and produces good quality output when
            used correctly. The CEO emphasised the following:<br>
            <br>
            The Claude Pro subscription held by each team member is a
            significant investment in the project. Every team member
            must use it effectively and to its full capability to
            accelerate FSD generation, IST review, and SP analysis. The
            tool is available — the quality of output depends on the
            quality of input. Developers must engage Claude with the
            actual source code, stored procedure SQL, and specific
            context, not generic descriptions.<br>
            <br>
            Common issues encountered during the two weeks and
            techniques to overcome them were discussed. These included
            providing the complete form code to Claude for Stage 0
            analysis, submitting SP SQL via Follow-up Prompt B for
            proper code-based analysis, and using the structured IST
            questionnaire to guide Seenivasan and Palanivel's field
            experience responses.<br>
            <br>
            <b>5. Technology Stack — Reporting Tool Decision</b><br>
            <br>
            Abinandan presented findings from the FastReports vs
            QuestPDF evaluation. The ASP.NET Core 8 code quality has
            been confirmed as good. The cost of FastReports paid version
            was discussed and the team agreed that QuestPDF, being free
            and code-driven, is the more appropriate choice for SPINRISE
            Phase 1.<br>
            <br>
            TL-Dev Sasi noted that it would be preferable to use a
            single tool that can handle not only PDF print output but
            also Excel and CSV data exports, to keep the reporting
            architecture consistent.<br>
            <br>
            <b>Decision: </b>QuestPDF is to be evaluated as the single
            reporting tool covering PDF, Excel, and CSV requirements.
            Abinandan will confirm the QuestPDF feedback and its
            capability for Excel/CSV output by Monday 13 April. EPPlus
            remains the current confirmed approach for Excel/CSV — this
            review will determine whether QuestPDF can replace it or
            whether the two-tool approach (QuestPDF for PDFs, EPPlus for
            Excel/CSV) is retained.<br>
            <br>
            The CEO noted that the first working SPINRISE PR print from
            Abinandan's POC confirms that the migration is achievable. <b>He
              expressed confidence in the team's ability to deliver.</b><br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <b>6. FSD Completion Commitment Before Next Meeting</b><br>
            <br>
            Each module developer committed to submitting FSDs for their
            respective module transactions before the next review
            meeting. The scope includes not just the first transaction
            but the subsequent transactions in each module that are part
            of Phase 1 scope. Completed FSDs must follow the checklist,
            pass PM sign-off, and be ready for CEO approval.<br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <b>7. Next Review Meeting</b><br>
            <br>
            The next SPINRISE Project Review Meeting is scheduled for <b>Friday,
              17 April 2026 at 5:00 PM</b> in the Meeting Room. Note:
            Saturday 18 April is the 3rd Saturday and a non-working day.<br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <b>8. Closing Remarks</b><br>
            <br>
            The CEO closed the meeting on a positive and motivating
            note. He reminded the team that the SPINRISE migration is a
            once-in-a-decade platform transformation for Kalpatharu
            Software. The clean FSD documents being prepared today are
            the foundation upon which the entire SPINRISE codebase will
            be built. The effort invested in documentation now will
            directly determine the quality, maintainability, and
            longevity of the migrated platform. Every team member is
            part of building something that will serve the company and
            its customers for the next decade. The CEO expressed pride
            in the team and confidence in the project's success with the
            dedication shown.<br>
            <br>
